
[1]enslave

   ENSLA'VE, v.t. [from slave.] To reduce to slavery or bondage; to
   deprive of liberty and subject to the will of a master. Barbarous
   nations enslave their prisoners of war, but civilized men barbarously
   and wickedly purchase men to enslave them.

   1. To reduce to servitude or subjection. Men often suffer their
   passions and appetites to enslave them. They are enslaved to lust, to
   anger, to intemperance, to avarice.
